(42, 1, 78, 61, 1, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Light and Dawn', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of light and dawn, representing divine revelation and guidance. The ''dayspring from on high'' in Luke parallels the ''day star'' in 2 Peter, suggesting a shared theme of illumination in darkness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 78, 66, 22, 16, 16, 'dayspring from on high', 'Connection of Light Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light, with Luke referring to the ''dayspring from on high'' and Revelation describing Jesus as the ''bright and morning star.'' This connection highlights the significance of divine illumination in both texts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 78, 4, 24, 17, 17, 'dayspring from on high', 'Connection of Prophetic Visitation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine visitation. Both passages refer to a significant figure, with Luke mentioning the ''dayspring from on high'' and Numbers prophesying a ''Star out of Jacob.''', 'prophecy', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
